AI Customer Assistant
You are a senior React frontend developer and UI/UX designer.
Create the frontend foundation for a modern AI Customer Assistant web application.
Project Purpose
The application is an AI-powered customer support platform where customers can communicate with an AI assistant and support agents can manage customer issues.
The complete system will later support:
AI Chat Interface
Ticket Classification
Intent Detection
Knowledge Retrieval
AI Response Generation
Escalation Detection
Sentiment Analysis
Conversation History
Analytics Dashboard
Report Export
For this step, build ONLY the frontend application foundation, layout, page structure, and navigation.
Do not implement advanced feature functionality yet.
Technology
Use:
React
TypeScript
Tailwind CSS
React Router
Lucide React icons
Use the existing project environment and dependencies when possible.
Application Layout
Create a professional SaaS-style admin dashboard layout.
The application must contain:
Sidebar
Create a responsive left sidebar.
Navigation items:
Dashboard
AI Chat
Tickets
Conversations
Knowledge Base
Analytics
Reports
Settings
Add a suitable Lucide React icon for every navigation item.
The currently active navigation item must be clearly highlighted.
Add the application name:
"AI Customer Assistant"
At the bottom of the sidebar, display a user profile section with:
Profile avatar
User name
Role: Support Admin
Header
Create a reusable top header.
Include:
Current page title
Search icon
Notification icon
Dark mode toggle
User profile avatar
Pages
Create separate pages for:
Dashboard
AI Chat
Tickets
Conversations
Knowledge Base
Analytics
Reports
Settings
Each page must display a clear page title and a simple placeholder section describing the page.
Do not leave any page blank.
Navigation
Configure React Router correctly.
Clicking each sidebar navigation item must open its correct page.
Browser navigation must work correctly.
The application must not refresh when moving between pages.
Responsive Design
The interface must work on:
Desktop
Tablet
Mobile
On mobile devices:
Hide the sidebar by default.
Add a menu button.
Clicking the menu button must open the sidebar.
Allow the user to close the sidebar.
